{
  "path": "/docs/appflow/package/credentials",
  "previousText": "Package Build Types",
  "previousUrl": "/docs/appflow/package/build-types",
  "nextText": "Adding Credentials",
  "nextUrl": "/docs/appflow/package/adding-credentials",
  "body": [
    "div",
    null,
    [
      "p",
      {
        "class": "intro"
      },
      "Security Profiles securely store your credentials so you can easily reference\nthem when building your app in the cloud."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "h2",
      {
        "id": "overview"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "#overview"
        },
        "Overview"
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "You'll need two sets of Apple certificates when your app goes to production,\nwhich means you'll eventually need two Security Profiles: one for development\nand one for production."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "We'll guide you through creating a development profile with the credentials\nthat you need for the desired platform below."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "h2",
      {
        "id": "android-credentials"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "#android-credentials"
        },
        "Android Credentials"
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "The ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "https://developer.android.com/training/articles/keystore.html"
        },
        "Android keystore"
      ],
      ", used for signing apps, can be generated using keytool, which is included in the ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/jdk8-downloads-2133151.html"
        },
        "Java JDK"
      ],
      ". Change ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "MY-RELEASE-KEY"
      ],
      " and ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        "MY_ALIAS_NAME"
      ],
      " to be relevant to your app. The tool will ask you to enter a keystore password and a key password."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "docs-code",
      {
        "language": "shell"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "pre",
        null,
        [
          "code",
          null,
          [
            "span",
            {
              "class": "token prompt"
            },
            "$ "
          ],
          "keytool -genkey -v -keystore MY-RELEASE-KEY.keystore -alias MY_ALIAS_NAME -keyalg RSA -keysize ",
          [
            "span",
            {
              "class": "token number"
            },
            "2048"
          ],
          " -validity ",
          [
            "span",
            {
              "class": "token number"
            },
            "10000"
          ],
          " -storetype jks"
        ]
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "h2",
      {
        "id": "ios-credentials"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "#ios-credentials"
        },
        "iOS Credentials"
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "You'll need an Apple Developer account (Individual or Organization). See ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "https://developer.apple.com/support/compare-memberships/"
        },
        "comparing\nmemberships"
      ],
      "."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "h3",
      {
        "id": "registering-your-app-id"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "#registering-your-app-id"
        },
        "Registering your App ID"
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "Every app must register an ID with Apple."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "ul",
      null,
      " ",
      [
        "li",
        null,
        "Navigate to ",
        [
          "a",
          {
            "href": "https://developer.apple.com/account/ios/identifier/bundle"
          },
          "Certificates, Identifiers & Profiles › Identifiers › App IDs"
        ],
        " in the ",
        [
          "a",
          {
            "href": "https://developer.apple.com/account"
          },
          "Apple Developer Center"
        ],
        " and register a new App ID."
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      [
        "img",
        {
          "src": "/docs/assets/img/appflow/ss-profiles-ios-app-id.png",
          "alt": "iOS App id"
        }
      ]
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "ul",
      null,
      " ",
      [
        "li",
        null,
        "Under Explicit App ID, set the Bundle ID to the ID you've specified in your app's ",
        [
          "code",
          null,
          "config.xml"
        ],
        " file. iOS Bundle IDs are represented as a reversed address, such as ",
        [
          "code",
          null,
          "com.ionicframework.MyIonicApp"
        ],
        "."
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "h3",
      {
        "id": "device-registration"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "#device-registration"
        },
        "Device Registration"
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "Devices must be explicitly registered with Apple for sending push notifications during development."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "ul",
      null,
      " ",
      [
        "li",
        null,
        "Navigate to ",
        [
          "a",
          {
            "href": "https://developer.apple.com/account/ios/device/"
          },
          "Certificates, Identifiers & Profiles › Devices › All"
        ],
        " in the ",
        [
          "a",
          {
            "href": "https://developer.apple.com/account"
          },
          "Apple Developer Center"
        ],
        " and register a new Device."
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      [
        "img",
        {
          "src": "/docs/assets/img/appflow/ss-profiles-ios-device-register-1.png",
          "alt": "iOS Register Device"
        }
      ]
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "ul",
      null,
      " ",
      [
        "li",
        null,
        "Give your device a name and enter the device's UDID. ",
        [
          "a",
          {
            "href": "ios-udid"
          },
          "Find your UDID"
        ],
        "."
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "h3",
      {
        "id": "certificate-signing-request"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "#certificate-signing-request"
        },
        "Certificate Signing Request"
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "Before you can get a certificate from Apple, you'll need to generate a certificate signing request file. It can be created on Mac OSX by using Keychain Access and on other platforms by using OpenSSL."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "h4",
      {
        "id": "using-keychain-access"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "#using-keychain-access"
        },
        "Using Keychain Access"
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "ul",
      null,
      " ",
      [
        "li",
        null,
        "Navigate to Keychain Access › Certificate Assistant › Request a Certificate From a Certificate Authority on your Mac."
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      [
        "img",
        {
          "src": "/docs/assets/img/appflow/ss-profiles-ios-csr.png",
          "alt": "iOS CSR"
        }
      ]
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "ul",
      null,
      " ",
      [
        "li",
        null,
        "Enter your name and email address. Leave the CA Email blank."
      ],
      " ",
      [
        "li",
        null,
        "Select Saved to disk and hit continue. This will generate your ",
        [
          "code",
          null,
          ".certSigningRequest"
        ],
        " file."
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "h4",
      {
        "id": "using-openssl"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "#using-openssl"
        },
        "Using OpenSSL"
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "ul",
      null,
      " ",
      [
        "li",
        null,
        "Generate a private RSA key file."
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "docs-code",
      {
        "language": "shell"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "pre",
        null,
        [
          "code",
          null,
          [
            "span",
            {
              "class": "token prompt"
            },
            "$ "
          ],
          "openssl genrsa -out keyname.key ",
          [
            "span",
            {
              "class": "token number"
            },
            "2048"
          ]
        ]
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "ul",
      null,
      " ",
      [
        "li",
        null,
        "Create the certificate signing request file by filling out the interactive form."
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "docs-code",
      {
        "language": "shell"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "pre",
        null,
        [
          "code",
          null,
          [
            "span",
            {
              "class": "token prompt"
            },
            "$ "
          ],
          "openssl req -new -key keyname.key -out CertificateSigningRequest.certSigningRequest"
        ]
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "h3",
      {
        "id": "ios-app-certificate-provisioning-profile"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "#ios-app-certificate-provisioning-profile"
        },
        "iOS App Certificate & Provisioning Profile"
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "Before you can generate App Certificates & Provisioning Profiles, you'll need to ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "#ios-setup"
        },
        "register your app and any devices, and obtain a ",
        [
          "code",
          null,
          ".certSigningRequest"
        ]
      ],
      "."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "App Certificates & Provisioning Profiles are for signing your app and giving it access to certain devices."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "h4",
      {
        "id": "certificate"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "#certificate"
        },
        "Certificate"
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "There are two types of Apple certificates: development and production. We'll guide you through generating credentials with a development certificate."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "ul",
      null,
      " ",
      [
        "li",
        null,
        "Navigate to ",
        [
          "a",
          {
            "href": "https://developer.apple.com/account/ios/certificate/development"
          },
          "Certificates, Identifiers & Profiles › Certificates › Development"
        ],
        " in the ",
        [
          "a",
          {
            "href": "https://developer.apple.com/account"
          },
          "Apple Developer Center"
        ],
        " and create a new certificate. Under Development, select iOS App Development."
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      [
        "img",
        {
          "src": "/docs/assets/img/appflow/ss-profiles-ios-cert-1.png",
          "alt": "iOS Cert"
        }
      ]
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "ul",
      null,
      " ",
      [
        "li",
        null,
        "Step through the steps. Upload the ",
        [
          "code",
          null,
          ".certSigningRequest"
        ],
        " you created to generate a certificate. Then, download your certificate. It should be a ",
        [
          "code",
          null,
          ".cer"
        ],
        " file."
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "Next, we'll need to convert the certificate from a ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        ".cer"
      ],
      " file to a ",
      [
        "code",
        null,
        ".p12"
      ],
      " file. It can be converted on Mac OSX by using Keychain Access and on other platforms by using OpenSSL."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "h4",
      {
        "id": "using-keychain-access"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "#using-keychain-access"
        },
        "Using Keychain Access"
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "ul",
      null,
      " ",
      [
        "li",
        null,
        "Drag your ",
        [
          "code",
          null,
          ".cer"
        ],
        " file into your login keychain."
      ],
      " ",
      [
        "li",
        null,
        "Right click on your imported certificate and click Export."
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      [
        "img",
        {
          "src": "/docs/assets/img/appflow/ss-profiles-ios-cert-2.png",
          "alt": "iOS Cert"
        }
      ]
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "ul",
      null,
      " ",
      [
        "li",
        null,
        "Select Personal Information Exchange (.p12) for File Format."
      ],
      " ",
      [
        "li",
        null,
        "Save the certificate, giving it a strong password."
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "h4",
      {
        "id": "using-openssl"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "#using-openssl"
        },
        "Using OpenSSL"
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "ul",
      null,
      " ",
      [
        "li",
        null,
        "Download your iOS certificate to the same directory as your private RSA key."
      ],
      " ",
      [
        "li",
        null,
        "Change the format of the iOS certificate to PEM."
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "docs-code",
      {
        "language": "shell"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "pre",
        null,
        [
          "code",
          null,
          [
            "span",
            {
              "class": "token prompt"
            },
            "$ "
          ],
          "openssl x509 -inform DER -outform PEM -in ios_development.cer -out ios_development.cer.pem"
        ]
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "ul",
      null,
      " ",
      [
        "li",
        null,
        "Export the certificate as a ",
        [
          "code",
          null,
          ".p12"
        ],
        " file, giving it a strong password."
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "docs-code",
      {
        "language": "shell"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "pre",
        null,
        [
          "code",
          null,
          [
            "span",
            {
              "class": "token prompt"
            },
            "$ "
          ],
          "openssl pkcs12 -export -inkey keyname.key -in ios_development.cer.pem -out Certificates.p12"
        ]
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "h3",
      {
        "id": "provisioning-profile"
      },
      " ",
      [
        "a",
        {
          "href": "#provisioning-profile"
        },
        "Provisioning Profile"
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      "Provisioning profiles give your app access to be installed, or ",
      [
        "em",
        null,
        "provisioned"
      ],
      ", on specific devices. For iOS App Development provisioning profiles, devices are selected manually."
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "ul",
      null,
      " ",
      [
        "li",
        null,
        "Navigate to ",
        [
          "a",
          {
            "href": "https://developer.apple.com/account/ios/profile/limited"
          },
          "Certificates, Identifiers & Profiles › Provisioning Profiles › Development"
        ],
        " in the ",
        [
          "a",
          {
            "href": "https://developer.apple.com/account"
          },
          "Apple Developer Center"
        ],
        " and create a new provisioning profile."
      ],
      " "
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "p",
      null,
      [
        "img",
        {
          "src": "/docs/assets/img/appflow/ss-profiles-ios-pp-1.png",
          "alt": "iOS Provisioning Profile"
        }
      ]
    ],
    " ",
    [
      "ul",
      null,
      " ",
      [
        "li",
        null,
        "Under ",
        [
          "strong",
          null,
          "Development"
        ],
        ", select ",
        [
          "strong",
          null,
          "iOS App Development"
        ],
        "."
      ],
      " ",
      [
        "li",
        null,
        "Select the correct App ID (with the Bundle ID matching your app's ",
        [
          "code",
          null,
          "config.xml"
        ],
        " file)"
      ],
      " ",
      [
        "li",
        null,
        "Select the certificate you generated."
      ],
      " ",
      [
        "li",
        null,
        "Select any and all development devices."
      ],
      " ",
      [
        "li",
        null,
        "Download the ",
        [
          "code",
          null,
          ".mobileprovision"
        ],
        " file, which is your provisioning profile file."
      ],
      " "
    ]
  ],
  "title": "Generating Credentials",
  "headings": [
    {
      "text": "Overview",
      "href": "#overview"
    },
    {
      "text": "Android Credentials",
      "href": "#android-credentials"
    },
    {
      "text": "iOS Credentials",
      "href": "#ios-credentials"
    }
  ],
  "pageClass": "page-appflow-package-credentials"
}
